# Actix-web Framework Best Practices

- Use modular application structure with separate modules
- Implement proper middleware for cross-cutting concerns
- Use Application Data for shared state management
- Organize routes in separate modules by domain
- Use proper extractors for request data (Json, Query, Path)
- Implement comprehensive error handling with custom error types
- Use async handlers for I/O bound operations
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes
- Implement authentication and authorization middleware
- Use logging middleware for request tracking
- Add CORS middleware for cross-origin requests
- Implement rate limiting and security headers
- Use connection pooling for database connections
- Implement proper transaction management
- Use async database drivers (sqlx, sea-orm)
- Handle database errors appropriately
- Write integration tests for API endpoints
- Use actix-web test utilities
- Mock external dependencies in tests
- Test error scenarios and edge cases
- Use streaming responses for large data
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use compression middleware
- Monitor application metrics and performance
